description: The daughters of Freya are the descendants of the mythical female warriors of the Amazon River and they are carrying out an insane plan to become absolute mistresses of a world populated exclusively by women. Martin, Java and Diana try to foil this plot with the help of an old friend from Manaus: Jerry Drake, otherwise known as Mister No!
name: L'impero Segreto

description: After eighteen years Martin Mystère resumes the investigation into the death of Morel, the archaeologist killed by the Men in Black many years before. In the mean time new facts emerge which seem to connect his assassination to a bizarre adventure experienced by Lawrence of Arabia in the thirties and to the mysterious death of Albert Aubrey, the author of a popular gossip column …
name: "Strano ma Vero!"

description: With the return of Martin and Java to Kalabaka, the previous adventure is concluded, but not before Professor Mystère and loyal Java have come up against another obscure enigma. Immediately afterwards, there begins a fascinating journey around magical Ireland, in search of the secret of the Book of Kells, a precious medieval illuminated manuscript. Two brothers, Lillian and Sean, come to the aid of Martin and Java in this quest, and they seem to have a personal interest in the Book…
name: Il Libro di Kells

description: A relentless hunt for two brothers, that has endured for over four centuries: Sean and Lillian are being chased down by a harsh and ruthless enemy … An enemy who wants to put an end to the enchanted world of Faerie and of all the Elves of Ireland . The brothers’ only hope of salvation is Martin Mystère, but the powerful necromancer who crosses his path has more than one arrow to his bow…
name: Un Altro Mondo

description: A chain of impossible robberies throw the museums into confusion. Mysterious individuals, living to an incredible age, purloin all the existing versions of “ The island of the Dead ”, the famous painting by the Swiss artist Arnold Böcklin. Perhaps it’s simply a question of a mania of that has taken hold of inveterate collectors, but this is only a vain hope and the Detective of the Impossible knows this. How can thieves be stopped if they are literally able to disappear into thin air ? And what secret is hidden in the stolen paintings ?
name: L'isola dei Morti

description: Hans Von Balthasar, the Alchemist, believed he had discovered the secret of immortality. But entelechy, the substance he and his assistants have taken, gives side effects that only Böcklin’s painting can block. They thought they would live forever, they thought they held the world in their hands, but instead, only by crossing the threshold which leads to Elsewhere, beyond the painting, can they escape from the terrible curse which has become their life … A threshold that even Mystère is forced to cross to free himself from this dark enigma .
name: Oltre la Soglia

The Voynich manuscript is a coded text from the thirteenth century that has resisted every attempt to read it. This document forms the basis for an adventure where Martin Mystère finds himself up against a fanatic telepreacher, satellite killers, Benedictine and Franciscan monks, artificial intelligence, the Men in Black, Atlantis and a sinister threat that is preparing to destroy the entire planet!
name: Obiettivo Apocalisse

description: Martin and Java are up against the mystery of Jack the Ripper, the first serial killer of the modern era who, in 1888, killed at least five women and whose identity was never officially ascertained. The mysterious crimes begin again in our times, and the truth the Detective of the Impossible discovers turns out to be linked to the terrifying Myths of Cthulhu!
name: Il Ritorno di Jack

description: Boris Grigov is an elderly Russian refugee who has fled to Nice. Nobody knows where his wealth and the exceptional vitality he shows come from. Grigov is obsessed with the death of the Tsar’s family, which he witnessed as a boy. Thanks to a clairvoyant, he manages to evoke the spirit of one of the Romanovs’ daughters. Together with her, however, the shadow of Rasputin appears as well, and begins to pursue the old man. But Mystère, who is in Nice together with Grigov’s grandson, suspects that underneath it all there is some kind of scam.
name: L'enigma di Boris Grigov

description: Rasputin, the “Mad Monk” adviser to the family of the Tsars, is the adversary whom Martin Mystère must confront in the final chapter of this adventure. It is set in Nice, but originates in Russia at the beginning of the century, in the twilight years of Romanov power. The reason for this dispute is the Stone of Life, a jewel with supernatural powers that Rasputin wants at all costs!
name: La Pietra Della Vita

description: Rorschach’s ten marks make up the most powerful psychological projective test that exists. When the genial psychologist Hermann Rorschach created these marks, in 1921, he made fifteen marks…What was the real objective of the complete series? What happened to the last five marks? Who, since then, has been using them? Why does someone want to stop Mystère from helping Gino Casiraghi, a wheeler-dealer from Milan who maintains he has found the missing marks?
name: Le Macchie di Rorschach
